body:
Am I the only one hoping for this? Normally the hero is just average good man with powers and the villain is the biggest asshole in the 3rd dimension.

http://clevermusings.net/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/spops3mdama.jpg

Examples
{{champion:127}} 
She&#039;s just racist, that&#039;s her entire character. She just hates everything that isn&#039;t like her.

{{champion:58}} 
A pretty cool guy until he had to hear Xerath&#039;s terrible singing voice for thousands of years and became a savage killing machine. 

{{champion:36}} 
This guy is just a murder. I don&#039;t even know how he even got into the league originally, he just flat out murders people in the streets and uses them for his experiments.

{{champion:134}} 
She was discovered to have crazy power that could go horrible wrong. Proves everyone right -_-

{{champion:90}}
Is basically Anakin Skywalker. He knows terrible things were going to happen in the future but instead of being the one man to stop them he just joins the problem.

I think it would be cool to get more grey area characters like those of Noxus. Darius wants what's best for his people. People can like him because he's out for his fellow man. Nautilus in a way isn't a villain at all, he's just a guy who got left behind and wants revenge. He's reasonably pissed, another reason why he's one of my favorite champions. The majority of champions I own is only because of how they are in lore. I find it hard to side with the person who's argument for justice is an eye for an eye. With that logic everyone should be a slave again because Africans weren't ever the only slaves and aren't the last. slavery is still a thing today yet people seem to go a little blind to it. Kind of messed up right.

